===2020 census===
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], Corley had a population of 31, with 15 households and 13 families. The [[population density]] was 518.9 inhabitants per square mile (200.3/km<sup>2</sup>). There were 16 housing units at an average density of 267.8 per square mile (103.4/km<sup>2</sup>). All residents lived in rural areas.<ref name="Census2020DP">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic Profile (DP1)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dp?get=NAME,DP1_0021P,DP1_0024P,DP1_0025C,DP1_0049C,DP1_0045C,DP1_0069C,DP1_0073C,DP1_0125P,DP1_0126P,DP1_0129P,DP1_0133P,DP1_0137P,DP1_0138P,DP1_0139P,DP1_0141P,DP1_0142P,DP1_0143P,DP1_0145P,DP1_0146P,DP1_0147C,DP1_0148C,DP1_0149C,DP1_0156C,DP1_0157C,DP1_0158C,DP1_0159P,DP1_0160P&for=place%3A16320&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref><ref name="Census2020PL">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Redistricting Data (Public Law 94-171)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/pl?get=NAME,P1_001N,P1_003N,P1_004N,P1_005N,P1_006N,P1_007N,P1_008N,P1_009N,P2_001N,P2_002N,H1_001N,H1_002N&for=place%3A16320&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref><ref name="Census2020DHC">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics (DHC)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dhc?get=NAME,P2_002N,P2_003N&for=place%3A16320&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2023|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

There were 15 households, of which 6.7% had children under the age of 18 living with them. Of all households, 73.3% were married-couple households, 6.7% were cohabitating couples, 6.7% had a male householder with no spouse or partner present, and 13.3% had a female householder with no spouse or partner present. About 13.3% of households were non-families, 13.3% were made up of individuals, and 6.7% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

The median age was 64.5 years. 3.2% of residents were under the age of 18. By broader age ranges, 12.9% of residents were under the age of 20, 0.0% were from 20 to 24, 6.5% were from 25 to 44, 38.7% were from 45 to 64, and 41.9% were 65 years of age or older. The gender makeup was 54.8% male and 45.2% female. For every 100 females there were 121.4 males, and for every 100 females age 18 and over there were 114.3 males age 18 and over.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

Of the 16 housing units, 6.2% were vacant. The homeowner vacancy rate was 0.0% and the rental vacancy rate was 0.0%.<ref name="Census2020DP"/><ref name="Census2020PL"/>

